The plastics look good with just normal scuffs and wear. If I recall correctly there is one very small crack in one of the black trim pieces. The Kimber Ultra Crimson Carry II is a 3" barrel .45ACP 1911 paired with a full- size frame and includes Crimson Carry red dot laser grips. The melded forged steel slide and lightweight alloy frame fit together with tight tolerances and function perfectly. Recoil on the Kimber Custom Ultra Carry II feels significantly less than that of competing designs. This is due in part to this pistol’s lower center of gravity, which is slightly below the slide, and very close to where the shooter's hand grips the gun. Although the single-stack magazine puts the Kimber's capacity at only eight rounds, the relatively small diameter of the 1911's frame still allow the shooter to create a secure two-handed grip. 

The Kimber Pro Crimson Carry II includes a lightweight aluminum alloy frame to reduce weight for concealed carry. Crimson Trace laser grips provide instant squeeze activation and deliver a decisive advantage in low light situations. A match grade barrel and bushing deliver tack driving accuracy. For added reliability, Kimber includes a full- length guide rod, as the shorter G.I. style guide rods have a tendency to bind or break over time. Snag-free, low profile front and rear iron sights sit on top of the slide and provide a consistent target presentation. The checkering on the mainspring housing, plus the texture of the laser grips feel secure.The knurled extended magazine release of the Kimber Pro Crimson Carry II is a huge improvement over releases seen on other pistols. Performing tactical reloads is quick, simple and efficient. 

The Kimber Pro Crimson Carry II single stage, match grade aluminum trigger is a joy to pull, especially over the mushy triggers seen on most double action pistols. The 4 – 5 lbs pull is steady and smooth, while the reset is short and crisp. This is a gun that fires naturally, even for beginner's that have “low and left” trigger slap tendencies. In fact, the Kimber Pro Crimson Carry II has one of the smoothest trigger pulls of any production 1911 on the market.. Other features includes an ambidextrous paddles. Finally, to further minimize felt recoil, the grip safety is a high-ride beavertail style designed to quickly establish a positive grip for maximum control under stress fire conditions.
